"We have to find the instructors," Mira said, her eyes darting toward the exit. "If there’s one of those things here, there are more. My staff is... it’s dead, Ren. The crystal is cracked."
Ren looked at her staff. Through his new vision, it wasn't just a cracked crystal. He saw the 'Logic' of the item.
[Item: Resonance Staff (Damaged)]
[Integrity: 12%]
[Fault: Void-Contamination in the core.]
"Give it to me," Ren said.
"What? Ren, we need to move—"
"Give it to me. I can bypass the safety and get a one-time pulse. We need to know if the path to the bus is clear."
Mira hesitated, then handed him the staff. As Ren’s fingers touched the wood, a blue screen flickered in the corner of his eye.
[Skill Trigger: Structural Deconstruction]
[Target: Resonance Staff]
[Action: Purge Contamination? (Cost: 5 MP)]
Yes, Ren thought.
A faint, microscopic spark jumped from his thumb into the staff. Mira didn't see it, but she gasped as the dull, grey crystal suddenly flared with a pure, white light. The cracks didn't disappear, but they stopped glowing with that sickly green Void-rot.
"It's back?" Mira whispered, taking it back. "How did you—?"
"Loose wiring," Ren lied, already turning toward the door. "Let's go."
They stepped out of the department store ruins back into the yellow fog. But the Site 9 they had arrived at was gone. The skyscrapers that had been half-finished were now complete, but they were made of that same black, pulsing data Ren had seen earlier.
"The bus should be three hundred meters that way," Jax pointed toward a wall of fog.
"No," Ren said, his eyes narrowing.
In his vision, the fog wasn't just weather. It was a shroud of 'Error Codes.' And standing right in the middle of their path back to the instructors was a figure.
It looked like Instructor Graves. He was standing perfectly still, his back to them.
"Instructor!" Jax called out, his voice cracking with relief. "Over here! We were attacked by a—"
"Jax, wait," Ren grabbed the back of Jax’s vest.
The figure turned. It was Graves, but his face was wrong. His eyes were missing, replaced by two perfectly circular holes that emitted the same low-frequency hum Ren had heard at the Gate.
