The "Graves" figure opened its mouth, and instead of words, the sound of a school bell rang out—the exact bell from Aethelgard Academy.
"Class is in session," the figure said, the voice a perfect, chilling mimicry.
Behind the figure, a dozen more shapes began to materialize in the fog. They weren't monsters. They were students. Students with no faces, all wearing the Academy uniform, all holding weapons made of solidified shadow.
"Ren," Mira whispered, backing away. "What is this? This isn't a training exercise."
Ren felt the silver mark on his hand burn. The system screen flared bright red, filling his entire field of vision.
[Emergency Quest Updated: The Traitor's Banquet]
[Objective: Protect the 'Survivors'.]
[Hidden Objective: Identify the 'Administrator' among the Faculty.]
"Stay behind me," Ren said.
"You're a Zero!" Jax yelled, panic finally taking over. "What are you going to do with a wrench and a dead scanner?!"
Ren didn't answer. He reached out into the empty air, and for the first time, he didn't look at the world. He looked at the code beneath it.
"I'm going to find the exit," Ren said.
The world is officially breaking. Ren is the only one who can see the 'truth' behind the illusion.
